  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    ForMod
    Normally the code generator will infer the mod id and mod class from your `@Mod` annotation.
    Model
    Can be attached to public static non-final fields with the type IBakedModel.
    ModElement  
    NoReg
    Exclude a field from automatic registration.
    Param
    Can be used to specify the class and field where to find codecs.
    PrimaryConstructor
    This is used to create very simple Codecs for classes.
    RegisterClass
    This can only be used in LibX is added as an annotation processor! Apply to a class to register all public static final fields to a ModXRegistration To ignore a field add @NoReg to it.
    RegisterConfig
    Automatically registers a LibX config.
    RegName
    Set custom name for registration
